Lewis lung carcinoma induced mouse (C57/BL6) model. The recombinant peptide was 
confirmed to be displayed on the surface of M13 phage as an extension for 
phage's PVIII protein. Immunization of mice with peptide-phage vaccine resulted 
in antibody production against EM-L2 and significant reduction of tumor growth 
rate by nearly 25 percent. In conclusion, EM-L2 displaying phage particles could 
be deemed as an encouraging strategy in contemporary cancer immunotherapy.

