Erratum in
    Health Promot Chronic Dis Prev Can. 2019 Feb;39(2):64.

We quantified the contributions of leading causes of death and drug overdose to 
changes in life expectancy at birth over time and inequalities by sex and 
socioeconomic status in British Columbia. From 2014 to 2016, life expectancy at 
birth declined by 0.38 years and drug overdose deaths (mainly opioid-involved) 
contributed a loss of 0.12 years of the decrease. The analysis also demonstrated 
that the higher drug overdose mortality among males and among those in lower 
socioeconomic status communities contributed to a differential decrease in life 
expectancy at birth for males and for those in the latter category.

